            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I don't like the formatting where there is major indentation on all lines, everything gets very crowded at the right.  Instead, move the first argument to a new line as well and use normal wrapping rules.  The automatic wrapping detection in tools like PyCharm's formatter produces some weird lines, so manually verify that the lines actually look good.\n\n``` python\n# from\npermanent_session_lifetime = ConfigAttribute('PERMANENT_SESSION_LIFETIME',\n                                             get_converter=_make_timedelta)\n# to\npermanent_session_lifetime = ConfigAttribute(\n    'PERMANENT_SESSION_LIFETIME',\n    get_converter=_make_timedelta\n)\n```\n\nAlso, can we disable the line length, or at least extend the it the modern guideline of 100 characters?  I've never been a fan of the 80 character hard limit, and it would alleviate the wrapping problem described above.\n\nThere are still some instances of `\\` continuation.\n"
        },
