            "created_at": "2017-04-13T22:27:01Z",
            "updated_at": "2017-04-13T22:28:22Z",
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Closing this due to large number of merge conflicts. Unless we can close all other outstanding PRs first, I don't think a blanket change is the way to go, as it has a high potential of causing merge conflicts. Strategy I see going forward:\r\n\r\n* Do some GitHub / git magic and figure out what files are not part of any open PR, and fix those.\r\n* Add a tox test that filters flake8's output based on the lines git reports as changed and only fails if changed lines have lint issues. See [git-lint](https://github.com/sk-/git-lint/), for example, although it hasn't been updated recently and does not support flake8.\r\n* In the meantime, just be a bit more rigorous about new PRs. We can push changes to newly-submitted PRs, and can re-submit old ones if we want to help it along."
